{"TopicId":131886,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Tiny Lander help","CreatedByName":"Nich","CreatedById":145678,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-11T18:10:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nich","CreatedById":145678,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-11T18:10:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I use SAS it holds a heading fine but when I attempt to hold propagrade or retrograde it dances all over the place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Lh0kOJJ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022Lh0kOJJ.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-11T18:19:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222404016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022131886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455214252\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145678\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nich\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Nich said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I use SAS it holds a heading fine but when I attempt to hold propagrade or retrograde it dances all over the place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Lh0kOJJ.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Lh0kOJJ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Lh0kOJJ.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe current SAS code is bugged as it used to be way before version 1.0. The only way to stop that wobble is to use less torque. Annoyingly the only small parts with low levels of torque are the two larger HEX probe cores. The wheel you have is too strong for a craft that small.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-11T19:13:23Z\u0022 title=\u002202/11/2016 07:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-11T21:12:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUmm, just a thought...how about adding the smallest probe core and controlling from it? I\u0027ve had odd things happen when the only thing to control a craft is a command seat\u002BKerbal.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}